race.description: Highview Accounting & Financial Pinker Pinker Plate
race.comment: MORRISSETTE (2) on top in the Pinker Pinker Plate. She's racing in super form for Reece Goodwin, narrowly beaten in a pair of BM78s at her past two outings. She found the line well behind a Group class mare in She's A Hustler at Flemington last time out and rates highly off that effort. ALMA RISE (1) was just fair fresh at Sandown Hillside but will strip much fitter. She probably needs one more run but her best would likely win this. Wary. BRAVE MISS (4) is racing in consistent form and was narrowly behind MORRISSETTE last time out. In the mix again. JEALOUS (6) modest effort first up last start, finishing sixth and beaten 1.5 lengths over 1600m at Sandown-Hillside. Fitter and can feature.
